    <div class="parent-container">
        <section class="travel-advice">
            <h2>Advice & Travel Planning</h2>
            <div class="advice-container">
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Travel Advice for Your India Trip</h3>
                    <p>Explore India's travel advice and tips based on our firsthand experience from numerous trips to the country, both as tourists and on business. This will hopefully assist you in planning your trip.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>What Do I Need to Pack?</h3>
                    <p><strong>Which clothing?</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Check temperatures to bring the right clothing.</li>
                        <li>November to February can be cold, getting down toward freezing in some parts.</li>
                        <li>March onwards can be warm and very warm; no jumpers required.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p><strong>What about electrical accessories?</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Obtain a surge protection plug for your chargers and computers.</li>
                        <li>We experienced the loss of a camera charger that almost spoiled our trip.</li>
                        <li>One helpful businessman in Delhi opened early to allow us to purchase a replacement.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>India Accommodation Guide</h3>
                    <p>India offers a huge range of accommodation from the highest levels of luxury to more basic options. Overall, the quality you get for your money is extremely high. Here are a few notes to help you choose based on my personal experience:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Research online reviews before booking.</li>
                        <li>Consider location and accessibility to attractions.</li>
                        <li>Look for deals and discounts on booking platforms.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Tipping in India Advice</h3>
                    <p>Tipping can make many people feel awkward due to uncertainty about whether it is appropriate and how much to tip. Here are a few guidelines:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>10-15% is standard in restaurants.</li>
                        <li>Round up taxi fares or add a small amount for drivers.</li>
                        <li>Tip hotel staff for good service.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Travel Advice in India</h3>
                    <p>Having been to India numerous times and heavily involved in planning trips for others, we provide some guidelines on planning your itinerary and travel:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Plan your itinerary based on regions to minimize travel time.</li>
                        <li>Consider local festivals and events for a richer experience.</li>
                        <li>Stay flexible to adapt to local conditions.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Staying Connected in India</h3>
                    <p>Staying connected while on your India holiday is a priority for most people. Here are a few tips:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Purchase a local SIM card for affordable data and calls.</li>
                        <li>Use Wi-Fi in hotels and cafes to save on data.</li>
                        <li>Download offline maps and travel apps for convenience.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Indian National Parks Advice</h3>
                    <p>We love wildlife and have visited many Indian Tiger parks. Here are some notes on how to get the most from your time in Indian parks:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Book safaris in advance, especially during peak seasons.</li>
                        <li>Follow park rules and respect wildlife.</li>
                        <li>Bring binoculars and a good camera for wildlife viewing.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Eating Out in India</h3>
                    <p>Food in India is generally very good and great value, with a huge variety of places to eat out. Here are our tips:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Choose busy restaurants for better food safety.</li>
                        <li>Try local specialties for an authentic experience.</li>
                        <li>Drink bottled water to avoid stomach upsets.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>Shopping in India Advice</h3>
                    <p>India is a fabulous place to shop, with a huge range of high-quality goods on offer. Here are some tips:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Negotiate prices in local markets.</li>
                        <li>Look for authentic handicrafts and textiles.</li>
                        <li>Be cautious of counterfeit goods in tourist areas.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
        
                <div class="advice-item">
                    <h3>India's Climate</h3>
                    <p>India has a diverse climate that varies significantly across regions. Here are some key points:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>The best time to visit is generally from October to March when the weather is cooler and more pleasant.</li>
                        <li>Be prepared for the heat in the summer months (April to June).</li>
                        <li>Expect monsoon rains in many areas from June to September.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

    </div>
